\\nLayout\\n\\t•\\tHeader: \u003cReference\u003e + back arrow to Home\\n\\t•\\tSubtitle: \u003cBook Chapter:Verse(s)\u003e\\n\\t•\\tProgress bar (same as Home but interactive tooltip on tap)\\n\\t•\\tMechanics dropdown (always visible, always fully expanded in wireframes):\\nMechanics listed vertically:\\n\\t1\\tWord Bank\\n\\t◦\\tL1, L2, L3, L4, L5\\n\\t2\\tWord Scramble\\n\\t◦\\tL1–L5\\n\\t3\\tType First Letter\\n\\t◦\\tL1–L5\\n\\t4\\tType Full Word\\n\\t◦\\tL1–L5\\n\\t5\\tRecite Out Loud\\n\\t◦\\tL1–L5\\nGating Rules\\n\\t•\\tMechanics strictly linear\\n\\t•\\tA mechanic’s L1 is locked until the previous mechanic’s L5 is passed\\n\\t•\\tWithin a mechanic, L(N) is locked until L(N–1) passed\\n\\t•\\tLocked \u003d visible but greyed\\n\\t•\\tPassed \u003d blue checkmark\\n\\t•\\tCurrent \u003d highlighted blue\\n\\t•\\tReplay \u003d tapping any completed level reopens it (no change to progress)\\n\\n4. MECHANIC WIREFRAMES (5 MECHANICS)\\n\\n4.1 WORD BANK (L1–L5)\\nScreen layout\\n\\t•\\tHeader: Word Bank L#\\n\\t•\\tVerse text with missing words replaced by blank chips\\n\\t•\\tWord bank panel at bottom with draggable/selectable words\\nBehavior\\n\\t•\\tUser taps or drags words into blanks\\n\\t•\\tImmediate success/failure per blank\\n\\t•\\tZero errors required to pass\\n\\t•\\tOn pass → “Level cleared—Continue”\\n\\t•\\tOn any error → “Try again”\\nL1–L5 progression pattern\\n\\t•\\tIncreasing number of missing words\\n\\t•\\tIncreasing difficulty (longer words, key theological terms)\\n\\n4.2 WORD SCRAMBLE (L1–L5)\\nPattern chosen: Scramble entire verse into a pool\\nScreen layout\\n\\t•\\tHeader: Word Scramble L#\\n\\t•\\tLarge empty canvas showing the verse as empty slots\\n\\t•\\tBottom grid: scrambled word tiles\\n\\t•\\tUser taps tiles in correct order\\nBehavior\\n\\t•\\tWrong tap \u003d immediate fail\\n\\t•\\tZero errors required\\n\\t•\\tDifficulty escalates by increasing total scrambled words\\n\\n4.3 TYPE FIRST LETTER (SYSTEM AUTO-FILLS WORD)\\nScreen layout\\n\\t•\\tHeader: Type First Letter L#\\n\\t•\\tVerse line-by-line\\n\\t•\\tEach missing word appears as a blank\\n\\t•\\tKeyboard present\\nBehavior\\n\\t•\\tUser types the first letter\\n\\t•\\tApp completes the entire word automatically\\n\\t•\\tWrong first letter \u003d immediate fail\\n\\t•\\tZero errors required\\nDifficulty scaling\\n\\t•\\tMore blanks per level\\n\\t•\\tHarder words blanked at higher levels\\n\\n4.4 TYPE FULL WORD\\nLayout\\n\\t•\\tHeader: Type Full Word L#\\n\\t•\\tVerse text with blanks\\n\\t•\\tKeyboard present\\nBehavior\\n\\t•\\tUser types each full missing word\\n\\t•\\tAutocorrect disabled\\n\\t•\\tAny typo \u003d fail\\n\\t•\\tPass on zero errors\\n\\t•\\tDifficulty increases by number of missing words\\n\\n4.5 RECITE OUT LOUD\\nPattern chosen: Random missing-word pauses\\nLayout\\n\\t•\\tHeader: Recite Out Loud L#\\n\\t•\\tVerse text shown normally\\n\\t•\\tAudio playback with waveform\\n\\t•\\tPlayback automatically pauses on random missing words\\n\\t•\\tLarge microphone button appears during pauses\\nBehavior\\n\\t•\\tUser says the missing word\\n\\t•\\tApp listens on-device only (no upload)\\n\\t•\\tApp compares speech-to-text result to expected word\\n\\t•\\tAny mismatch \u003d fail\\n\\t•\\tZero errors \u003d pass\\nDifficulty\\n\\t•\\tMore pauses per level\\n\\t•\\tHarder words chosen randomly from curated difficulty pool\\n\\n5. POP QUIZ FLOWS\\n\\n5.1 FILL-IN L5 POP QUIZ\\nSame interface as Type Full Word, but:\\n\\t•\\tAll blanks appear at once\\n\\t•\\tNo hints\\n\\t•\\tZero errors required\\n\\t•\\tOnce passed → mark Pop Quiz # (3d / 7d / 14d / 30d) as completed\\n\\n5.2 VOICE L5 POP QUIZ\\nSame as Recite Out Loud L5, but:\\n\\t•\\tRandomized pauses across entire verse\\n\\t•\\tNo retries mid-quiz\\n\\t•\\tZero errors required\\n\\t•\\tPassing completes the scheduled quiz slot\\n\\n6. HAMBURGER MENU\\nOrder:\\n\\t1\\tMy Armor\\n\\t2\\tFull Armor Sets\\n\\t3\\tArmor by Topic\\n\\t4\\tCustom Armor\\n\\t5\\tSetting